The paper deals with image deconvolution, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves optimization techniques, such as convex quadratic constrained linear programming, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for image deconvolution, which can be considered as a contribution to cs.MM (Multimedia). The proposed method also involves regularization, which is a common topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
